chunk_content: If errors are identified in data, these should be remediated at the point of service delivery as well as in the PEPFAR and host-country reporting systems as soon as possible. More specifically, as many countries are approaching the UNAIDS 95-95-95 goals, it is more important than ever to understand exactly how many people living with HIV are receiving treatment. Furthermore, it is imperative that countries understand the treatment gaps remaining by location and population to ensure that all PLHIV have equitable access to treatment and are virally suppressed, and that scarce resources are allocated appropriately to areas with the greatest unmet need. As such, we are at a very important moment in the HIV response where accuracy of the data is essential in ensuring that programmatic decisions are made effectively. PEPFAR is committed to ensuring that the data collected through the MER are accurate and timely.
